      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark mb-4">Nursing Care Plan Template</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">A nursing care plan is divided into 5 main sections. This five-section represents the nursing process which is the diagnosis, planning, implementation, and evaluation.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">In simple terms, a nursing care plan will just walk you through the nursing process.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">A care plan is outlined with five columns, and in each column, you include the nursing process. Let walk through what you include in each of this section.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">1) Assessment column</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">In the assessment column of the nursing care plan template. You should write all of the assessment data that you've compiled from your patient. You should assess your patient thoroughly and write down all of that assessment on the assessment column that supports your diagnosis. The data can be divided into subjective and objective data. Subjective data are things you can't really prove while objective is things that can prove or observe.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">2) Nursing diagnosis</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The second column of the nursing care plan template is the nursing diagnosis. This should be a complete nursing diagnosis including the</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li class="text-gray-700">NANDA @international standardized nursing diagnosis</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">The related to factor (r/t)</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">As evidenced by section (aeb) supporting evidence.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You should look at the books to support the most</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">3) The planning column</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The planning column of the nursing care plan can be the most challenging for most nursing students. Here you are supposed to write your patient goals or outcomes. You should write what you want the patient to achieve. When coming up with the goals, you need to ensure the Goals are SMART(Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound). The outcomes also need to be patient-centric i.e It's written as to what the patient will do not what the nurse will do. To make sure the goals are patient-centric each goal should be started with "The Patient Will…"</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">4) Implementation</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The next part is the implementation part of the care plan template. The Implementation has two parts</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li class="text-gray-700">Actual nursing intervention</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">The rationale</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The nursing intervention should be written as to what the nurse will do to help the patient meet the goals. It should be started with "The nursing student will…"</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Next to the nursing intervention, you will write why you choose these interventions (rationale). It should be evidence-based and backed by research.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">5) The Evaluation</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You will decide if the patient has met the goals, and if not what you intend to change to meet the goals in the future. If the patient has met the goals, New goals should be met.</p>
